    },
    {
      "id": "407457752f7296442a9fcaa8c468f9d54db57e4f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 140,
        "name": "jacques-Charles Lafoucriere",
        "email": "jacques-charles.lafoucriere@cea.fr",
        "username": "jcl"
      },
      "date": "2013-09-18 20:35:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nThe logic I suggest in my last comment is what I will do. Today the without +/- mode is like the last one overide all the previous. Based on my last proposal, which logic do you prefer?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "bc0b866b5c267972210337a657c66582e775603c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-09-18 22:35:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> New logic: -- +P1 +P2: add P1 and P2 -- +P1 -P2: add P1 remove P2 -- P1 P2: set to P1 and P2 -- P1 -P2: set to P1 remove P2 => result is P1 -- -P1 P2: remove P1 add P2 I can also forbid a mix of P and +/-P so 4 and 5 forbidden\n\nIn fact I don't care so much about the exact details, so long as we are not too surprising. Let's support the same style as /proc/sys/lnet/debug:\n\n 1) 'echo foo bar > file' means that only foo and bar are set.\n 2) 'echo +foo bar > file' means that foo and bar are set in addition to whatever was set before.\n 3) 'echo -foo bar > file' means that foo and bar are now unset but all other bits are unchanged.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "8b95b144f5f3a1e8c415412afd75fc63490bbbd7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 140,
        "name": "jacques-Charles Lafoucriere",
        "email": "jacques-charles.lafoucriere@cea.fr",
        "username": "jcl"
      },
      "date": "2013-09-19 06:35:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nI will set only if no sign are used in all the string so\n1) +P1 +P2: add P1 and P2\n2) +P1 -P2: add P1 remove P2 \n3) P1 P2: set to P1 and P2 \n4) P1 -P2: add P1 remove P2 = same as +P1 -P2\n5) -P1 P2: remove P1 add P2 = same as -P1 +P2",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
